# Field Label Case (`meta.labelCase`)

Admin-configured `labelCase` on `form_options` fields controls **both** the label text AND the displayed value for every field in every table, wizard, and package block. The implementation is non-obvious and has one critical bug trap.

If your task touches **any** of the following, STOP and read
[`.cursor/skills/field-label-case/SKILL.md`](mdc:.cursor/skills/field-label-case/SKILL.md)
**before** writing code:

- Adding any table, list, or card that displays field labels or values from `form_options`
- Adding or editing `applyLabelCase` / `applyCaseToText` in any file
- Editing the `fieldLabelCases` build loop in `PoliciesTableClient.tsx`
- Adding a new column type to `PoliciesTableClient` that renders text from snapshots
- Debugging "Name shows UPPER CASE / wrong case / title case not working"
- Adding `labelCase` support to a new surface (endorsements table, agents table, etc.)

## The 30-second cheatsheet

| Concern | Pattern | Don't do |
|---|---|---|
| Title-case transform | `text.toLowerCase().replace(/\b\w/g, c => c.toUpperCase())` | `text.replace(/\b\w/g, c => c.toUpperCase())` — leaves ALL-CAPS unchanged |
| Load `labelCase` from API | Include `meta` in the fetch type; build a `cases: Record<string, labelCase>` map | Ignore `meta`; use raw label only |
| Apply to cell value | `applyCase(String(v), fieldLabelCases[path])` | Inline ternary per-cell |
| `_builtin.displayName` case | `getDisplayNameCase()` scans `fieldLabelCases` for `lastName`/`firstName`/`companyName` | Hard-code "title" or leave raw |
| Mutate stored data | ❌ Never — display-only transform | Writing transformed text to DB |
| Sorting / filtering | Use raw stored value | Sort/filter on transformed display string |
